          <p style="font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.2; color: #A9A7AF;"><i>Rescuers and volunteers evacuate a wounded person from an apartment building damaged during a Russian missile strike amid Russia's attack on Ukraine in Sumy. Credits: REUTERS/Stringer Purchase Licensing Rights
          </i></p>
        </mj-text> 

        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
         
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">US and Russian representatives met in Riyadh, Saudi Arabia, to <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-25-03-2025-h1-1-negotiate-a-potential-ceasefire?source=website" target="_blank">negotiate a potential ceasefire</a> in Ukraine behind closed doors. The White House says achieving security in the Black Sea to allow the free flow of shipping is a key purpose of the talks. The US delegation comprised Special Envoy for Ukraine Keith Kellogg and National Security Advisor Mike Waltz.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;filter:blur(5px);">Ukrainian FM Andrii Sybiha criticized Russia. While the talks were taking place, another missile hit Sumy and damaged several buildings, including a school, and 74 people were wounded. Sybiha stated that diplomacy with Russia "must be backed by firepower, sanctions, and pressure" to be effective. A Russian source told Reuters that a draft joint statement had been sent to Moscow and Washington for approval.
       </p>
        </mj-text>
